<TITLE> Tendulkar overtakes Lara as highest test runs scorer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOHALI, India, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India batsman Sachin Tendulkar became the highest test-run scorer on Friday when he passed his target of 15 runs in the first innings of his side's second test match against Australia. Tendulkar scored three runs after tea to move on to 16, giving him a career record of 11,955 runs to surpass the previous mark of West Indian Brian Lara. Lara had scored 11,953 runs before he retired from international cricket in 2007
